      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 53: `lastPushTime` and `lastCallPushTime` are updated from the Firebase service thread while deactivation scheduling/removal happens on the main handler. The volatile fields make individual reads visible, but the pair can still be observed inconsistently around `maxOf(...)`. Posting `notePushReceived` onto `backgroundHandler` would keep all lifecycle/deactivation state on one thread and simplify reasoning. Suggested direction:\n```suggestion\n    fun notePushReceived(isCallPush: Boolean) {\n        backgroundHandler.post {\n            val now \u003d SystemClock.elapsedRealtime()\n            lastPushTime \u003d now\n            if (isCallPush) lastCallPushTime \u003d now\n        }\n    }\n```",
