      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 145: Foreground reactivation is gated on `hasNetworkConnected()`, which can leave proxy-enabled accounts deactivated after the user opens the app while Android reports no connectivity or before connectivity state has refreshed. Since this method changes the account active flag, it should restore the foreground state regardless of current network availability so the daemon can reconnect when the network comes back. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\n                if (startedActivityCount++ \u003d\u003d 0\n                    \u0026\u0026 mPreferencesService.settings.enablePushNotifications\n                    \u0026\u0026 pushToken !\u003d null\n                ) {\n                    Log.d(TAG, \"App came to foreground — reactivating accounts\")\n                    mAccountService.setAccountsActiveForBackground(true)\n                }\n```",
