      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 83: Every high-priority FCM is treated as a call push. FCM priority is transport metadata and may also be used for non-call urgent messages, so this can unnecessarily keep accounts active for the longer 60s call grace window and trigger `connectivityChanged(true)`. Prefer classifying call pushes from explicit payload fields when available, and only fall back to priority for the known minimal DHT-proxy call payload shape. Suggested direction:\n```suggestion\n            val isCallPush \u003d isCallNotification || isDhtProxyCallWakeup(remoteMessage)\n```",
